   "source": [
    "# 1. What does RGBA stand for?\n",
    "\n",
    " An RGBA value is a tuple of 4 integers, each ranging from 0 to 255. RGBA color values are an extension of RGB color values with an alpha channel - which specifies the opacity for a color. An RGBA color value is specified with: rgba (red, green, blue, alpha)\n",
    " "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "67f776b8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 2. From the Pillow module, how do you get the RGBA value of any images?\n",
    " using getdata() function on the image object using Pillow module as done below\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "eec0dc42",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from PIL import Image\n",
    "\n",
    "im = Image.open(\"xyz.png\")\n",
    "im_alpha = im.convert('RGBA')\n",
    "Pixels = iter(im.getdata())\n",
    "for i in Pixels:\n",
    "    print(i)"
   ]
  },
